    To create a azure service principle using power shell folow the given points belows

1.use (az login) command to login/signin the account
2.After login/signin it will display the details in the powershell as shown in the below
      
     You have logged in. Now let us find all the subscriptions to which you have access...
[
  {
    "cloudName": "AzureCloud",
    "homeTenantId": "******************",
    "id": "****************",(this id we have to given in first command (az account set--subscription "id")
    "isDefault": true,
    "managedByTenants": [],
    "name": "Free Trial",
    "state": "Enabled",
    "tenantId": "***************",
    "user": {
      "name": "**********@gmail.com",
      "type": "user"
    }
  }
]

3.After showing these we have to run two commands
      a) az account set--subscription "id" (this command will help to set the id)
      b) az ad sp create-for-rbac -n "service name" (this command will help to create a service in azure)

4.After given the two commands our service is created susccessfully and displays the detalis like these

        Changing "az-service-principle" to a valid URI of "http://az-service-principle", which is the required format used for service principal names
Creating a role assignment under the scope of "/subscriptions/91cf4c35-ffd8-4abd-b9f2-c3cb35095de1"
  Retrying role assignment creation: 1/36
